  "chapter": {
    "number": 61,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Year of the LORD’s Favor"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Spirit of the Lord GOD is on Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because the LORD has anointed Me",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to preach good news to the poor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has sent Me to bind up the brokenhearted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to proclaim liberty to the captives",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and freedom to the prisoners,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2731
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to proclaim the year of the LORD’s favor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2732
          },
          {
            "text": "and the day of our God’s vengeance,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to comfort all who mourn,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to console the mourners in Zion—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to give them a crown of beauty for ashes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the oil of joy for mourning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a garment of praise for a spirit of despair.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So they will be called oaks of righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the planting of the LORD, that He may be glorified.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will rebuild the ancient ruins;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will restore the places long devastated;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will renew the ruined cities,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the desolations of many generations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Strangers will stand and feed your flocks,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and foreigners will be your plowmen and vinedressers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you will be called the priests of the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will speak of you as ministers of our God;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will feed on the wealth of nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will boast in their riches.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Instead of shame, My people will have a double portion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and instead of humiliation, they will rejoice in their share;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and so they will inherit a double portion in their land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and everlasting joy will be theirs.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I, the LORD, love justice;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I hate robbery and iniquity;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in My faithfulness I will give them their recompense",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and make an everlasting covenant with them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their descendants will be known among the nations,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their offspring among the peoples.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All who see them will acknowledge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that they are a people the LORD has blessed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will rejoice greatly in the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my soul will exult in my God;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for He has clothed me with garments of salvation",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wrapped me in a robe of righteousness,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as a bridegroom wears a priestly headdress,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as a bride adorns herself with her jewels.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For as the earth brings forth its growth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and as a garden enables seed to spring up,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so the Lord GOD will cause righteousness and praise",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to spring up before all the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
